The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses a deep neural network with recurrent residual learning, which falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of edge-preserving capability, which is a common technique in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of by-pass connections to speed up training convergence, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization (cs.NE).
